{
  "source": "../03-first-use-cli.md",
  "voice": "en-US-BrianNeural",
  "rate": "+5%",
  "total_duration": 82.032,
  "segments": [
    {
      "index": 0,
      "type": "voice",
      "text": "Let's use nexus for real. Everything here runs locally. No accounts, no API keys.\n\n### Memory",
      "over_screen": false,
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 8.616,
      "duration": 8.616
    },
    {
      "index": 1,
      "type": "voice",
      "text": "Memory is nexus's notepad. Store things by project. They survive across sessions.\n\nOne thing to know  \u2014  notes expire after 30 days by default. Add the permanent flag to keep them forever.",
      "over_screen": false,
      "start": 8.616,
      "end": 21.816,
      "duration": 13.2
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "type": "voice",
      "text": "Store, list, retrieve, search. That's the whole model.\n\n### Scratch",
      "over_screen": true,
      "start": 21.816,
      "end": 28.704,
      "duration": 6.888
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "type": "pause",
      "start": 28.704,
      "end": 29.704,
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "type": "voice",
      "text": "Scratch is like memory, but temporary. It lasts one session. Good for working notes and hypotheses.",
      "over_screen": false,
      "start": 29.704,
      "end": 37.072,
      "duration": 7.368
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "type": "voice",
      "text": "When the session ends, scratch is gone.\n\n### Index and Search",
      "over_screen": false,
      "start": 37.072,
      "end": 42.592,
      "duration": 5.52
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "type": "pause",
      "start": 42.592,
      "end": 43.592,
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "type": "voice",
      "text": "Now the main event. Semantic search. Regular search matches exact words. Nexus matches by meaning.\n\nFirst, we index a repo.",
      "over_screen": false,
      "start": 43.592,
      "end": 53.263999999999996,
      "duration": 9.672
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "type": "voice",
      "text": "That analyzed every file  \u2014  code, docs, everything  \u2014  and made it all searchable. Completely local.",
      "over_screen": true,
      "start": 53.263999999999996,
      "end": 59.72,
      "duration": 6.456
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "type": "pause",
      "start": 59.72,
      "end": 61.72,
      "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "type": "voice",
      "text": "Now let's search.",
      "over_screen": true,
      "start": 61.72,
      "end": 63.064,
      "duration": 1.344
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "type": "voice",
      "text": "The results found relevant code even when the exact words didn't match. That's semantic search. It matches by meaning, not by words.",
      "over_screen": true,
      "start": 63.064,
      "end": 71.848,
      "duration": 8.784
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "type": "pause",
      "start": 71.848,
      "end": 73.848,
      "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "type": "voice",
      "text": "Quick tip  \u2014  you can re-index automatically after every commit.",
      "over_screen": false,
      "start": 73.848,
      "end": 77.952,
      "duration": 4.104
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "type": "voice",
      "text": "Set it up once. Every commit keeps your search index fresh.",
      "over_screen": false,
      "start": 77.952,
      "end": 82.032,
      "duration": 4.08
    }
  ]
}